Execute only PHASE 08.1.

Goal:
Add database foundation, SQLAlchemy models, sessions, repositories, and lightweight migrations while preserving all in-memory fallbacks.

Create or update:
backend/app/db/__init__.py
backend/app/db/base.py
backend/app/db/session.py
backend/app/db/models.py
backend/app/db/repositories.py
backend/app/db/migrations.py
backend/app/core/config.py
.env.example
backend/app/tests/test_database_models.py

Requirements:
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.x style.
- Use UUID string primary keys.
- Use created_at and updated_at timestamps.
- Store JSON payloads using JSON-compatible columns.
- Keep SQLite compatibility for local development.
- Keep PostgreSQL compatibility for production.
- Development may use sqlite:///./zdash.db.
- Production should use PostgreSQL.
- In-memory stores from previous phases may remain as fallback.
- Database persistence should be preferred when enabled.
- No destructive migration behavior.

Models:
- users
- refresh_tokens
- audit_logs
- event_logs
- scheduler_jobs
- scheduler_runs
- halt_state
- backtest_results
- optimization_results
- content_items
- content_pipeline_runs
- iot_action_logs

Migration functions:
- run_migrations()
- create_all()
- check_database_connection()

Do not require Alembic unless full config is added cleanly.

Validation:
cd backend
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m ruff check app tests
python -B -m pytest -q

